AUDIO: 'Well, we\'re coming to the close of the year, but things do not seem to be slowing down just quite yet. Today, I\'m taking a look at Lumal Lab\'s new modify feature, which allows you to well, I mean, as the name implies, modify existing [music] video. Some good stuff'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here. Plus, are we getting our first look at V4? Well, maybe it\'s more like VO3.5, but there\'s a new mystery model floating around that just might be a Google surprise drop. We\'ll check into that today. and Topaz has updated Astra,'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'their video upscaler. I mean, I just happen to have early access, so we\'ll take a look at a bit of a preview today. Kicking off, Luma Labs have updated Ray 3 with a modify feature. Uh, this is'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'obviously a video to video function that allows you to add, remove, and restylize your input video, be it AI generated or not. Now, while we have seen this feature on a few other platforms,'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'notably, I think just a video or two ago on Cling, um, and listen, all of these can be a bit hit or miss, I will say that Luma has brought in their own, I mean, I guess flavor to this, uh, this particular feature, uh, such as the'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ability to modify with key frames. That is something that we haven\'t seen in the other versions of this. Kicking off with the briefest of overviews of how this works. Um, you know, simply hit the modify tab over here. That will open up'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the option for an image or a video. Drop your video in and then that will populate off the rest of the your option tabs essentially. Um you can of course just simply text prompt to uh you know modify your video. Uh we also have start'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'frames, a plus 5second frame which kind of acts as middle frame. Uh we\'re going to dig into that in a little bit and obviously character referencing. Below that, we have the strength slider, which'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'allows you to control the amount of influence that the model is going to take over your input video. So, you know, the lower it is, the more doggedly it\'s going to try to adhere to the uh, you know, whatever is happening in your'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'input video. The higher you go, um, the more allowance you\'re giving it to be creative. So, you might not get the exact same motions, but your fidelity might improve. And then finally in terms of your start frame and modify frames uh'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'if you have an image that you have like say nano bananed uh you would use start frame and then upload it. If you do not have it you can use modify frame that will open up luma\'s modify image feature which I mean essentially it\'s it\'s nano'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'banana as well. They all kind of do the same thing. So because there\'s I mean so much that you can do with a feature like this. We\'re going to start off on easy mode and then gradually work our way up to narrative. So kicking off with some stock drone footage of Dodger Stadium.'

